1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,500
These characters have no scripted dialogue.

2
00:00:03,500 --> 00:00:07,000
They talk, remember and change plans in real time —
driven by AI running on my own laptop.

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:11,500
Ordinary game NPCs repeat the same lines on a loop.

4
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:15,500
Here, every villager has memory,
a personality, and an agenda of their own.

5
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:20,000
A reimagining of Stanford's Generative Agents —
but fully offline, on an RTX 4060.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:25,000
I tell just one villager there's a party
at the plaza tonight.

7
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:30,000
No one else.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:35,000
And then word starts to spread.

9
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:40,500
Diego hears it from Maria,
and passes it on to Sofia.

10
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:45,500
Sofia tells Carlos.

11
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:52,000
Nobody coded that chain —
it emerges from their conversations.

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:57,000
By evening, the ones who heard
show up at the plaza — right on time.

13
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Five of five knew it;
four learned it by word of mouth.

14
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:08,000
Under the hood: a Python brain —

15
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:14,000
memory, relevance-based retrieval,
reflection, and planning.

16
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:20,000
It talks to Unity over WebSocket,
turn-based so a single GPU can run it.

17
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:24,000
No cloud. No APIs. No per-token cost.

18
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Just my GPU — and a village that comes alive.
